<exercise checkit-seed="0006" checkit-slug="SC3" checkit-title="Venn Diagrams">
    <statement>
        <p>
            A survey asks 500 people the following question: "Do you prefer horror movies or comedies?" In their answer, the respondents can specify one of the two options, both, or neither. Suppose 103 reported that they prefer horror movies only, 69 reported that they prefer comedies only, 221 reported that they prefer comedies, and 255 reported that they prefer horror movies.
            <ol>
                <li>Draw a Venn diagram of the situation. Use the information in the problem to clearly label the diagram.</li>
                <li>How many people  reported that they do not prefer horror movies?</li>
                <li>How many people  reported that they do not prefer comedies?</li>
            </ol>
        </p>
    </statement>
    <answer>
        <p>
            <ol>
                <li>In general you should draw overlapping circles contained in a larger rectangle. From the information given in this problem, 500 is the amount for the entire rectangle, 103 is the number for the crescent moon part of horror movies, 69 is the number for the crescent moon part of comedies, 221 is the number for the entire comedies circle, and 255 is the number for the entire horror movies circle.</li>
                <li>245 reported that they do not prefer horror movies.</li>
                <li>279 reported that they do not prefer comedies.</li>
            </ol>
        </p>
    </answer>
</exercise>
